Definition: a poisonous salt that forms dark purple crystals and is purple-red when dissolved in water
Example: used as an oxidizing and bleaching agent and as a disinfectant and antiseptic
Synonyms: permanganate_of_potash, permanganate, a, poisonous, salt, that, forms, dark, purple, crystals, and, is, purple-red, when, dissolved, in, water, used, as, an, oxidizing, bleaching, agent, disinfectant, antiseptic
Category: noun.substance
